<div class="section"><dl><dt><a title="addition" name="addition"></a></dt><h3><a href="/forms/collections/recommend.html"><strong>Suggest an Addition to the Library&apos;s Collection</strong></a></h3>
<dd>Is there an item you would like to see in the Library&apos;s collection? Order it with this form!</dd></dl></div>
<div class="section"><dl><dt><a title="visit" name="visit"></a></dt><h3><a href="/research/ref_ctr.html"><strong>Visit a Reference Center</strong></a></h3>
<dd>Bobst Library has a multidisciplinary reference desk on the first floor of the library where you can start your research, ask questions, and get subject-specific help from librarians. There are two main reference centers within the library, one devoted to the humanities and social sciences (first floor), and the other to business &amp; government information and physical &amp; life sciences (fifth floor).</dd></dl></div>
<div class="section"><dl><dt><a title="ask" name="ask"></a></dt><h3><a href="/ask/email.html"><strong>Ask a Librarian</strong></a></h3>
<dd>The Ask a Librarian service is a place to start your research, ask questions, and get subject-specific help from librarians. You can <a target="_blank" href="http://library.nyu.edu/ask/email.html">submit questions via e-mail</a> , <a target="_blank" href="http://library.nyu.edu/ask/">IM us from one of our pages</a> or by using screen name &quot;AskBobst,&quot; or text your questions to <TEL>646-265-1342</TEL>.</dd></dl></div><em></em>
<div class="section"><dl><dt><a title="contact" name="contact"></a></dt><h3><a href="/research/lib_arc.html"><strong>Contact a Subject Librarian or Archivist</strong></a></h3>
<dd>You may make an appointment to speak with a subject librarian regarding special research needs. Not sure who to ask? Use our <a target="_blank" href="http://library.nyu.edu/forms/research/consultations.html">consultation form</a> and we will match you with the appropriate librarian.&#160;</dd></dl></div>
<div class="section"><dl><dt><a title="fcm" name="fcm"></a></dt><h3><a href="http://www.nyu.edu/fcm/workrequestform/"><strong>Report a Problem with the Library&apos;s Facilities</strong></a></h3>
<dd>Use this online work request form to report a building issue to be fixed. e.g.: temperature issues, water fountains not working, cleaning a spill or bathroom issue. Note: type &quot;Bobst&quot; in the Building Search box, and select &quot;BOBST LIBRARY (70 Washington Square South)&quot;.</dd></dl></div>
<div class="section lastsection"><dl><dt><a title="borrow" name="borrow"></a></dt><h3><a href="/services/borrow_renew.html"><strong>Information About Borrowing, Renewing, Holding, or Recalling a Book</strong></a></h3>
<dd>Contact the circulation desk at <TEL>212-998-2500</TEL> (press &quot;2&quot;), or view the above frequently asked questions. You can also connect directly to your patron information from the link above.</dd></dl></div>
